<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-05-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-05-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="349" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d349">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">701.0090/126: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Bern</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-05-23">May 23, 1942</date>.<lb/>[Received May
                                    23—2:51 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>2260. American interests—Japan. Legation’s 2121, May 16 and
                                Department’s 1319, May 22. Swiss Minister Tokyo reports under date
                                May 21 that Japanese Government has decided to authorize
                                repatriation <pb facs="0436" n="424" xml:id="pg_424"/> of all
                                American newspaper correspondents without exception at present in
                                Japan and Japanese occupied parts China. Swiss Minister, Tokyo,
                                being requested to confirm that American newspaper correspondents
                                will be evacuated first exchange vessel.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Harrison</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>